definition:
Someone descended from Shuni who was a man of the tribe of Gad living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, first mentioned at Gen.46.16; 
 son of: Gad (H1410); 
 brother of: Ziphion (H6837), Haggi (H2291), Ezbon (H0675), Eri (H6179), Arod (H0720) and Areli (H0692)
Group of shu.ni (שׁוּנִי "Shuni" H7764) 
 § Shunites, of Shuna "fortunate"
 descendants of Shuni
